      • CHALLENGE

        public static final String CHALLENGE
        The challenge used to confirm the Arduino's identity. When this string is sent to the Arduino, the Arduino should reply with the value in RESPONSE, "youfoundme".

      • Arduino

        public Arduino(ArduinoCom c)
        throws IOException
        Makes a new Arduino by connecting to it over the specified ArduinoCom.
        Parameters:
        c - the ArduinoCom that provides a link to the Arduino.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem in the creation of I/O streams.

    • Method Detail

      • waitForWord

        public boolean waitForWord(long timeout,
                  String word)
                    throws InterruptedException
        Waits for the specified word to be read from the input stream. The timeout is passed into the readWord(long) method, and as such is the timeout for an individual word and not for the whole method.
        Parameters:
        timeout - the maximum amount of time to wait for a word (ms).
        word - the word to wait for (case sensitive).
        Returns:
        true if the specified word was found, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        InterruptedException - in the event that the wait is interrupted.

      • execute

        public ExecutionStatus execute(CommandSequence c)
        Executes the specified command sequence.
        Parameters:
        c - the command sequence to execute.
        Returns:
        true if all commands were received by the Arduino, false otherwise. If this method returns false, then it may not have sent all the commands to the Arduino.

      • execute

        public ExecutionStatus execute(Command c)
        Executes the specified command.
        Parameters:
        c - the command to execute.
        Returns:
        an ExecutionStatus object for getting information about the commands status.

      • execute

        private void execute(Command c,
           ExecutionStatus status)
        Executes the specified command and waits for either completion or an interrupt.
        Parameters:
        c - the command to execute.
        status - the status object to update with information about the command.

      • send

        public void send(String str)
        Sends the specified String to the Arduino using the println method in the output stream class. Also write the characters to the dataOut queue.
        Parameters:
        str - The string to send.

      • getSentData

        public Character getSentData()
                      throws IOException
        Gets the most recently send character. Blocks until data is available.
        Returns:
        the character that has been most recently sent to the Arduino using the send(String) method.
        Throws:
        IOException - when the stream is closed.

      • getReceivedData

        public Character getReceivedData()
                          throws IOException
        Get the most recent character that the Arduino has received. Blocks until data is available.
        Returns:
        the character that has been most recently received from the Arduino.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem reading data.

      • isArduinoConnected

        public boolean isArduinoConnected()
        Determines if an Arduino is connected. Uses the challenge and response identification scheme.
        Returns:
        true if the ArduinoCom is connected to an Arduino, false otherwise.

      • disconnect

        public void disconnect()
        Disconnects the Arduino by closing the I\O streams and closing the underlying ArduinoCom.

      • waitForByte

        public int waitForByte(long timeout)
                throws InterruptedException
        Waits for bytes to come into the input stream. Returns as soon as bytes are available or more time has passed than the specified timeout.
        Parameters:
        timeout - the maximum amount of time to wait for bytes, in ms.
        Returns:
        true if bytes are available, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        InterruptedException - if this thread is interrupted while waiting.

      • readWord

        public String readWord(long timeout)
                throws InterruptedException
        Reads the next word from the input stream. The words ends with either whitespace or a period of time of the specified length during which no data is received.
        Parameters:
        timeout - the maximum amount of time to wait for a byte (ms).
        Returns:
        the word, if it was received or null if no word was received.
        Throws:
        InterruptedException - in the event that the wait is interrupted.

      • getCom

        public ArduinoCom getCom()
        Gets the object used to communicate with the Arduino.
        Returns:
        the Arduino used to communicate with the Arduino.

      • getArduinoAt

        public static Arduino getArduinoAt(String loc)
        Gets the Arduino at the specified location. If there is no Arduino at the specdified location, returns null.
        Parameters:
        loc - the location, either a serial port name or an IP address.
        Returns:
        the Arduino at the specified location or null if there is no Arduino at the specified locaiton.
